# Agriculture Analytics - Intermediate Track
## Data Analytics Curriculum | 3-Month Program
### DataVerse Africa Internship Division | Cohort 4.0

---

## üìã **Program Overview**

**Duration:** 12 Weeks (3 Months)  
**Domain:** Agriculture & Agribusiness Analytics  
**Track Level:** Intermediate  
**Delivery Mode:** 100% Project-Based Learning  
**Industry Focus:** Farming Operations, Supply Chain, Market Intelligence, Agritech, Food Security, Rural Development  
**Target Outcome:** Agriculture data analysts ready for agribusiness companies, NGOs, government ministries, agritech startups, and research organizations

---

## üéØ **Agriculture-Specific Learning Objectives**

By the end of this track, interns will be able to:
- Analyze crop yield and production data
- Build farm performance and profitability dashboards
- Conduct market price analysis and forecasting
- Analyze agricultural supply chain efficiency
- Monitor food security and nutrition indicators
- Apply climate and weather data to agricultural decisions
- Build precision agriculture analytics solutions
- Understand agricultural policy and subsidy impact
- Create farmer profitability and cost-benefit models
- Communicate agricultural insights to farmers, policymakers, and investors

---

## üåæ **Core Agriculture Metrics Covered**

### **Production Metrics:**
- Crop Yield (tons per hectare)
- Total Production Volume
- Harvest Success Rate
- Planting vs. Harvesting Timeline
- Post-Harvest Loss Percentage
- Crop Quality Grades
- Land Utilization Rate
- Multi-cropping Index

### **Economic Metrics:**
- Farm Gate Prices
- Market Prices (wholesale, retail)
- Price Volatility Index
- Gross Margin per Crop
- Cost of Production per Hectare
- Return on Investment (ROI)
- Break-even Analysis
- Value Chain Markup Analysis

### **Efficiency Metrics:**
- Input-Output Ratio
- Labor Productivity
- Mechanization Rate
- Irrigation Efficiency
- Fertilizer Use Efficiency
- Seed-to-Harvest Cycle Time
- Storage Capacity Utilization
- Transportation Cost per Ton

### **Food Security Metrics:**
- Food Availability (kcal/capita/day)
- Food Access (household income vs food prices)
- Dietary Diversity Score
- Malnutrition Rates
- Food Price Index
- Import Dependency Ratio
- Strategic Reserve Levels

### **Environmental Metrics:**
- Water Usage per Crop
- Carbon Footprint
- Soil Health Indicators
- Pesticide Use Intensity
- Organic Matter Content
- Rainfall Variability

---

## üìä **Tools & Technologies Stack**

### **Primary Tools:**
- **Excel/Google Sheets:** Farm budgeting, crop budgets, profitability analysis
- **SQL:** Production records, market data analysis, farmer database queries
- **Power BI:** Farm performance dashboards, supply chain monitoring
- **Tableau:** Geographic mapping, market intelligence, climate visualization
- **Python (Optional but encouraged):** Yield prediction, price forecasting, climate analysis

### **Agriculture-Specific Tools:**
- **QGIS:** Geographic data and farm mapping (introduction)
- **Weather APIs:** Climate and weather data integration
- **FAO STAT:** Global agricultural statistics
- **Crop Calendars:** Seasonal planning tools
- **Market Information Systems:** Price tracking platforms

---

## üìÖ **12-Week Curriculum Structure**

---

### **MONTH 1: AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTION & FARM ECONOMICS**

---

#### **Week 1: Agriculture Analytics Foundations**

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Understand agricultural data ecosystem
- Master agriculture terminology and value chain
- Learn farming systems and crop production basics
- Navigate agricultural data sources

**Key Topics:**
- Agriculture sector overview (crops, livestock, fisheries, forestry)
- Agricultural value chain (input ‚Üí production ‚Üí processing ‚Üí distribution ‚Üí consumption)
- Farming systems (smallholder, commercial, organic, precision agriculture)
- Crop types and classifications (cereals, legumes, cash crops, horticulture)
- Seasonal patterns and agricultural calendars
- Agricultural data sources (FAO, national statistics, market systems, farm surveys)
- Data challenges in agriculture (scattered data, informal sector, seasonality)
- Sustainable agriculture and SDG indicators

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Case study: Analyzing FAO agricultural statistics for an African country
- Exercise: Mapping agricultural value chain for a specific crop (e.g., maize, cocoa)
- Exercise: Creating a crop calendar for a region

**Deliverable:** 
- **Mini Project 1:** "Agricultural Sector Overview Report"
  - Analyze 5-year agricultural production data for a country
  - Identify top 10 crops by production volume and value
  - Map the value chain for 2 major crops
  - 4-page report on sector trends and opportunities

**Tools:** Excel, Google Sheets, Tableau (for mapping)

---

#### **Week 2: Crop Yield & Production Analysis**

**üé§ DOMAIN EXPERT SESSION #1: "Data-Driven Agriculture: From Farm to Fork"**
- **Guest:** Agribusiness Data Manager / Agritech Startup Founder
- **Duration:** 90 minutes (Live Q&A)
- **Topics:** 
  - How data transforms modern farming
  - Precision agriculture and IoT sensors
  - Agritech opportunities in Africa
  - Career paths in agriculture analytics
- **Assignment:** Interns prepare questions based on Week 1 learnings

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze crop yield data and productivity trends
- Calculate yield per hectare across regions and farms
- Identify factors affecting crop performance
- Build production monitoring dashboards

**Key Topics:**
- Yield calculations (tons per hectare, bushels per acre)
- Total production vs. productivity analysis
- Yield gap analysis (actual vs. potential yield)
- Regional yield comparison
- Seasonal production patterns
- Factors affecting yield (rainfall, fertilizer, seed quality, labor)
- Multi-season and multi-crop analysis
- Production forecasting basics

**SQL Focus:**
- Aggregating production data by region, crop, season
- Date functions for agricultural seasons
- JOIN operations for farm, crop, and weather data
- GROUP BY for yield comparisons
- Window functions for year-over-year growth

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: 10,000+ farm production records across 3 years
- Exercise: Calculate average yield by crop and region
- Exercise: Identify high-performing vs. low-performing farms
- Exercise: Analyze seasonal production trends

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 1A:** "Crop Yield & Production Dashboard"
  - SQL queries to extract production metrics
  - Power BI dashboard showing:
    - Yield trends over time
    - Yield by region and crop type
    - Production volume comparison
    - Yield gap analysis
    - Top-performing farms
    - Seasonal production patterns

**Tools:** SQL, Power BI, Excel

---

#### **Week 3: Farm Profitability & Cost-Benefit Analysis**

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze farm economics and profitability
- Build crop budgets and enterprise budgets
- Calculate cost of production per hectare
- Understand farm input costs and returns

**Key Topics:**
- Farm income components (crop sales, livestock, off-farm income)
- Cost of production (seeds, fertilizer, labor, land preparation, harvest)
- Variable vs. fixed costs in farming
- Gross margin analysis per crop
- Net farm income calculations
- Break-even yield and price analysis
- Return on Investment (ROI) for farming enterprises
- Comparative profitability across crops

**Excel Advanced:**
- Farm budget templates
- Cost-benefit analysis models
- Sensitivity analysis for price and yield changes
- Scenario planning (drought, good harvest, price crash)

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: Farm input costs and output revenues for 500 farms
- Exercise: Build crop budget for maize and cassava
- Exercise: Calculate gross margin per crop
- Exercise: Identify most profitable farming systems

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 1B:** "Farm Profitability Analysis Suite"
  - Excel crop budget template (reusable)
  - Power BI dashboard with:
    - Revenue vs. cost analysis by crop
    - Gross margin comparison
    - Cost structure breakdown
    - ROI by farming enterprise
    - Break-even analysis
  - Written recommendations: Crop mix optimization (3 pages)

**Tools:** Excel (advanced), Power BI, SQL

---

#### **Week 4: Agricultural Market Price Analysis**

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze agricultural commodity prices
- Track price volatility and seasonality
- Compare farm gate vs. market prices
- Understand price transmission along value chain

**Key Topics:**
- Agricultural pricing fundamentals
- Farm gate prices vs. wholesale vs. retail prices
- Seasonal price patterns (lean season vs. harvest season)
- Price volatility and risk
- Price transmission analysis
- Market integration across regions
- Import vs. domestic prices
- Government price interventions (subsidies, price floors)

**Tableau Focus:**
- Time series price visualization
- Geographic price mapping
- Price correlation heatmaps
- Volatility charts

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: 3 years of weekly market prices for 10 crops across 20 markets
- Exercise: Calculate average prices by season
- Exercise: Identify price arbitrage opportunities
- Exercise: Analyze price volatility

**Deliverable:**
- **Major Project 1:** "Agricultural Market Intelligence Dashboard"
  - SQL queries for price analytics
  - Tableau dashboard with:
    - Price trends over time
    - Seasonal price patterns
    - Geographic price comparison (map)
    - Farm gate vs. retail price margins
    - Price volatility index
    - Price forecasting (simple moving average)
  - Market brief: Price outlook and trading opportunities (5 pages)
  - Presentation: 10-minute market intelligence briefing

**Tools:** Tableau, SQL, Excel

**Week 4 Checkpoint:** Portfolio Review & Mentor Feedback Session

---

### **MONTH 2: SUPPLY CHAIN & FOOD SECURITY ANALYTICS**

---

#### **Week 5: Agricultural Supply Chain Analysis**

**üé§ DOMAIN EXPERT SESSION #2: "Agribusiness Supply Chain Optimization"**
- **Guest Panel:** Supply Chain Manager (Agribusiness) + Logistics Analyst + Cold Chain Expert
- **Duration:** 2 hours (Panel + Workshop)
- **Topics:**
  - Post-harvest loss reduction strategies
  - Cold chain and storage analytics
  - Transportation optimization
  - How data improves supply chain efficiency
- **Interactive Activity:** Live case study - Optimize a tomato supply chain
- **Networking:** 30-minute Q&A on supply chain careers

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze agricultural supply chain efficiency
- Calculate post-harvest losses
- Monitor storage and warehousing performance
- Optimize transportation and logistics

**Key Topics:**
- Agricultural supply chain stages (harvest ‚Üí aggregation ‚Üí storage ‚Üí processing ‚Üí distribution)
- Post-harvest loss analysis (physical loss, quality deterioration)
- Storage capacity and utilization
- Cold chain monitoring
- Transportation cost per ton-kilometer
- Lead time analysis (farm to market)
- Inventory management in agriculture
- Supply chain bottleneck identification

**Power BI Focus:**
- Supply chain flow visualization
- Loss analysis at each stage
- Geospatial logistics mapping
- KPI scorecards for supply chain

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: Supply chain data for fresh produce (10,000 transactions)
- Exercise: Calculate post-harvest loss percentage
- Exercise: Analyze storage duration and quality degradation
- Exercise: Map transportation routes and costs

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 2A:** "Agricultural Supply Chain Efficiency Dashboard"
  - Power BI dashboard with:
    - Supply chain stage analysis
    - Post-harvest loss tracking
    - Storage utilization metrics
    - Transportation cost analysis
    - Lead time monitoring
    - Quality grade tracking
  - Supply chain optimization report with recommendations

**Tools:** Power BI, SQL, Tableau

---

#### **Week 6: Food Security & Nutrition Analytics**

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze food availability and access
- Monitor nutrition and dietary diversity
- Understand food security indicators
- Build early warning systems for food crises

**Key Topics:**
- Food security pillars (availability, access, utilization, stability)
- Caloric availability calculations
- Dietary diversity scores
- Household food security indicators
- Malnutrition rates (stunting, wasting, underweight)
- Food price vs. income analysis
- Coping strategies index
- Vulnerability analysis
- Early warning systems

**Advanced SQL:**
- Household-level food security calculations
- Aggregating nutrition surveys
- Regional food security classification
- Time-series crisis detection

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: Household food security survey (5,000 households)
- Exercise: Calculate dietary diversity scores
- Exercise: Classify households by food security status
- Exercise: Analyze food expenditure patterns

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 2B:** "Food Security Monitoring Dashboard"
  - Tableau dashboard with:
    - Food availability by region
    - Dietary diversity mapping
    - Malnutrition hotspot identification
    - Food price affordability index
    - Vulnerability classification
    - Trend analysis over time
  - Policy brief: Food security intervention priorities (4 pages)

**Tools:** Tableau, SQL, Excel

---

#### **Week 7: Climate, Weather, & Agricultural Risk Analysis**

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Integrate weather data with agricultural analysis
- Analyze climate impact on crop production
- Build drought and flood monitoring systems
- Understand agricultural insurance analytics

**Key Topics:**
- Climate variables affecting agriculture (rainfall, temperature, humidity)
- Rainfall variability and drought analysis
- Growing degree days (GDD) calculations
- Flood impact assessment
- Seasonal forecasting
- Climate change trends in agriculture
- Agricultural insurance (index-based, yield-based)
- Risk mitigation strategies

**Python Introduction (Optional):**
- Weather API integration
- Climate data visualization
- Correlation analysis (rainfall vs. yield)

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: 10 years of weather data + crop yield data
- Exercise: Analyze rainfall patterns and crop performance
- Exercise: Identify drought-affected regions
- Exercise: Calculate correlation between temperature and yield

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 2C:** "Climate-Smart Agriculture Risk Dashboard"
  - Tableau/Power BI dashboard with:
    - Rainfall pattern analysis
    - Drought monitoring (SPI index)
    - Temperature trends
    - Yield vs. rainfall correlation
    - High-risk zone identification
    - Climate change impact projections
  - Risk assessment report: Climate adaptation strategies

**Tools:** Tableau, Python (optional), Excel, SQL

---

#### **Week 8: Precision Agriculture & Technology Analytics**

**üé§ DOMAIN EXPERT SESSION #3: "Agritech & Digital Farming"**
- **Guest:** Precision Agriculture Specialist + AgTech Company Data Scientist
- **Duration:** 90 minutes
- **Topics:**
  - IoT sensors and farm data collection
  - Drone technology in agriculture
  - Machine learning for crop health
  - The future of smart farming in Africa
- **Demo:** Live walkthrough of precision agriculture platform
- **Career Insights:** Breaking into agritech analytics

**üíº BONUS: Industry Partner Showcase**
- **Partner:** Agritech startup or agricultural NGO
- **Activity:** Interns present their Week 1-7 projects to real agribusiness professionals
- **Feedback:** Professional critique and improvement suggestions
- **Opportunity:** Top performers may get interview or project opportunities

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Understand precision agriculture concepts
- Analyze sensor and IoT data
- Build farm management dashboards
- Understand variable rate application analytics

**Key Topics:**
- Precision agriculture technologies (GPS, sensors, drones, satellites)
- Soil testing and nutrient mapping
- Variable rate application (fertilizer, seed, irrigation)
- Crop health monitoring (NDVI, plant stress detection)
- Farm machinery telematics
- Yield mapping
- Decision support systems
- ROI of precision agriculture investments

**Power BI Advanced:**
- IoT data visualization
- Real-time monitoring dashboards
- Spatial analysis with maps
- Alert systems for threshold breaches

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: Simulated farm sensor data (soil moisture, temperature, crop health)
- Exercise: Analyze soil nutrient variability
- Exercise: Build irrigation recommendation system
- Exercise: Calculate ROI of precision farming investment

**Deliverable:**
- **Major Project 2:** "Precision Farming Analytics Platform"
  - Power BI dashboard with:
    - Farm field mapping
    - Soil health variability maps
    - Crop health monitoring (NDVI)
    - Irrigation scheduling recommendations
    - Fertilizer application optimization
    - Equipment utilization tracking
  - Business case: ROI analysis for precision agriculture adoption
  - Executive presentation (15 minutes)

**Tools:** Power BI, Tableau, SQL, Python (optional)

**Week 8 Checkpoint:** Mid-Program Review & Portfolio Update

---

### **MONTH 3: AGRIBUSINESS STRATEGY & CAPSTONE PROJECT**

---

#### **Week 9: Agricultural Policy & Impact Analysis + Capstone Planning**

**üéØ CAPSTONE PROJECT LAUNCH**
- **Capstone Kickoff Session:** Introduction to final project requirements
- **Project Selection:** Interns choose their capstone topic by end of week
- **Proposal Submission:** 2-page project proposal with scope, objectives, datasets
- **Mentor Assignment:** Each intern paired with dedicated capstone mentor

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Analyze agricultural policy interventions
- Assess subsidy program effectiveness
- Conduct impact evaluation basics
- Understand agricultural development programs
- Plan comprehensive capstone project

**Key Topics:**
- Agricultural policy types (subsidies, price supports, trade policies)
- Input subsidy programs (fertilizer, seed)
- Extension services and farmer training
- Agricultural credit programs
- Impact evaluation methods (before-after, with-without)
- Policy cost-benefit analysis
- Smallholder farmer support programs
- Agricultural transformation strategies

**Tableau Focus:**
- Policy impact visualization
- Geographic program coverage mapping
- Beneficiary analysis
- Outcome tracking

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Dataset: Fertilizer subsidy program data (10,000 beneficiary farmers)
- Exercise: Analyze program reach and coverage
- Exercise: Compare yields of beneficiaries vs. non-beneficiaries
- Exercise: Calculate program cost per farmer

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 3A:** "Agricultural Policy Impact Assessment"
  - Tableau dashboard with:
    - Program coverage and beneficiaries
    - Geographic distribution of interventions
    - Yield impact analysis
    - Cost-effectiveness metrics
    - Program success indicators
  - Policy brief: Recommendations for program improvement
- **Capstone Proposal:** Detailed project plan for Weeks 10-12

**Tools:** Tableau, SQL, Excel

---

#### **Week 10: Agricultural Market Intelligence & Storytelling + Capstone Development (Phase 1)**

**üé§ DOMAIN EXPERT SESSION #4: "Data for Agricultural Transformation"**
- **Guest:** Ministry of Agriculture Policy Advisor or FAO/World Bank Agriculture Specialist
- **Duration:** 2 hours
- **Topics:**
  - How data informs agricultural policy and investment
  - Communicating with government and donors
  - Case study: Data-driven agricultural program in Africa
  - The role of analytics in achieving food security
- **Workshop:** Interns present an agricultural issue analysis to the guest as if presenting to policymakers
- **Feedback:** Professional critique on policy communication

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Build farmer-facing and policy-maker-facing reports
- Create agricultural investment pitch decks
- Master agricultural data storytelling
- Communicate insights to diverse audiences (farmers, government, investors)
- Execute capstone data collection and cleaning phase

**Key Topics:**
- Agricultural data storytelling frameworks
- Building dashboards for different audiences
- Farmer extension materials (simplified insights)
- Investor pitch decks for agribusiness
- Government policy briefs
- NGO project proposals with data
- Visual storytelling for rural audiences

**Communication Focus:**
- Farmer advisory reports
- Government policy briefs
- Investor presentations
- NGO project proposals

**Capstone Phase 1 (Week 10):**
- Data collection and exploration
- Data cleaning and validation
- Initial SQL queries and database setup
- Preliminary agricultural analysis
- **Checkpoint:** Mid-capstone review with mentor (end of week)

**Hands-On Activities:**
- Exercise: Convert technical analysis into farmer advisory
- Exercise: Create 3 versions of same insight for different audiences
- Exercise: Peer review and feedback sessions

**Deliverable:**
- **Project 3B:** "Agricultural Communication Portfolio"
  - Farmer advisory dashboard (simple, visual)
  - Government policy brief (data-driven, 5 pages)
  - Investor pitch deck (10 slides)
  - Infographic for rural extension workers
  - Video presentation (5 minutes) on agricultural opportunity
- **Capstone Checkpoint:** Data ready, preliminary insights documented

**Tools:** Power BI, Tableau, PowerPoint, Canva

---

#### **Week 11: Capstone Development (Phase 2) - Analysis & Visualization**

**üé§ CAREER PREPARATION PANEL (Week 11, Day 1)**
- **Guests:** Agribusiness Recruiters + Recent Alumni in Agriculture Analytics Roles
- **Duration:** 2 hours
- **Activities:**
  - Mock interviews with real recruiters
  - Resume and LinkedIn profile reviews
  - Salary negotiation workshop for agriculture sector
  - Job search strategy session
- **Outcome:** Each intern gets personalized career action plan

**Capstone Phase 2 (Week 11):**
- Complete all agricultural analysis and modeling
- Build all dashboards and visualizations
- Develop comprehensive report (first draft)
- Create presentation slides
- **Daily Stand-ups:** 15-minute daily check-ins with mentors
- **Peer Review Session (Mid-week):** Interns present work-in-progress to peers for feedback
- **Technical Review (End of week):** Mentor validates analysis and methodology

**Weekly Milestones:**
- Day 1-2: Complete all agricultural analysis and calculations
- Day 3-4: Build interactive dashboards
- Day 5-6: Write comprehensive agricultural report
- Day 7: Technical review and refinements

**Mentor Support:**
- Office hours every day
- Slack channel for quick questions
- Query/formula review sessions
- Domain expertise consultation

---

#### **Week 12: Capstone Finalization & Final Presentations**

**Capstone Phase 3 (Week 12, Days 1-4):**
- Finalize all deliverables
- Polish dashboards and visualizations
- Complete final agricultural report (15-20 pages)
- Prepare presentation (20-minute talk)
- Create video walkthrough
- Update GitHub repository with documentation
- Build LinkedIn portfolio showcase post
- **Final Rehearsal (Day 4):** Practice presentation with mentors

**Capstone Final Week Schedule:**

**Day 1-2: Refinement & Quality Check**
- Incorporate mentor feedback from Week 11
- Final data validation
- Dashboard performance optimization
- Proofread agricultural report

**Day 3: Preparation & Rehearsal**
- Finalize presentation slides
- Practice delivery timing
- Prepare for technical Q&A
- Final mentor review

**Day 4: Dress Rehearsal**
- Full presentation run-through with mentors
- Technical setup testing
- Last-minute adjustments

**Day 5: üèÜ CAPSTONE FINAL PRESENTATIONS**
- **Audience:** Domain experts, mentors, industry partners, DataVerse leadership, fellow interns, agribusiness professionals
- **Format:** 20-minute presentation + 10-minute Q&A per intern
- **Schedule:** 4-5 presentations per session (morning & afternoon sessions)
- **Judging Panel:** Agricultural economists, Agribusiness CEOs, Ministry officials, NGO leaders, Agritech founders
- **Evaluation Criteria:**
  - Agricultural accuracy and rigor (30%)
  - Business/policy impact and recommendations (25%)
  - Visualization quality and clarity (20%)
  - Communication effectiveness (15%)
  - Innovation and creativity (10%)

**Awards & Recognition:**
- ü•á Best Overall Capstone Project
- üå± Most Innovative Agricultural Solution
- üìä Best Agricultural Dashboard
- üí¨ Best Agricultural Storytelling
- üåç Highest Rural Impact Potential

**Post-Presentation:**
- Networking mixer with agricultural professionals (1.5 hours)
- One-on-one conversations with potential employers
- Group celebration and certificate ceremony
- Official program completion

**Final Deliverables Due (Day 5, before presentations):**
- Interactive Power BI/Tableau agricultural dashboards (published online)
- Comprehensive agricultural analysis report (PDF, 15-20 pages)
- SQL scripts and data queries
- Excel models and calculations
- Presentation slides (PowerPoint/Google Slides)
- Video walkthrough (5-7 minutes)
- GitHub repository with full documentation
- LinkedIn portfolio post
- Project README file

